{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Adrian Beria Blog","author":"Adrian Beria"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"f20fbfba-5f1b-5ebd-9841-fe593159b1b3","excerpt":"According to the documentation: Redux is a predictable state container for JavaScript apps. Its generally used with React when we need to…","html":"<p>According to the documentation:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Redux is a predictable state container for JavaScript apps.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Its generally used with React when we need to make our state available for the whole app. The global state is stored inside an object tree called <strong>STORE</strong> and the only way to make changes (Create, Update and Delete) is with <strong>ACTIONS</strong> which is an object describing the change in the main state using <strong>REDUCERS</strong> which says how it will change.</p>\n<p>Lets start with a simple example to showcase how it works before going into a project.</p>\n<p>Lets create the store:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5f72283d6e5e9cbd5006cc45a6e9e9c0/f42d4/redux-overview-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 61.58663883089771%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/5f72283d6e5e9cbd5006cc45a6e9e9c0/fb8a0/redux-overview-1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5f72283d6e5e9cbd5006cc45a6e9e9c0/1a291/redux-overview-1.png 148w,\n/static/5f72283d6e5e9cbd5006cc45a6e9e9c0/2bc4a/redux-overview-1.png 295w,\n/static/5f72283d6e5e9cbd5006cc45a6e9e9c0/fb8a0/redux-overview-1.png 590w,\n/static/5f72283d6e5e9cbd5006cc45a6e9e9c0/526de/redux-overview-1.png 885w,\n/static/5f72283d6e5e9cbd5006cc45a6e9e9c0/f42d4/redux-overview-1.png 958w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Now lets try a reducer:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d189c87b2058252663fecf595debcb01/7bc9a/redux-overview-2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 59.25297113752123%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/d189c87b2058252663fecf595debcb01/fb8a0/redux-overview-2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d189c87b2058252663fecf595debcb01/1a291/redux-overview-2.png 148w,\n/static/d189c87b2058252663fecf595debcb01/2bc4a/redux-overview-2.png 295w,\n/static/d189c87b2058252663fecf595debcb01/fb8a0/redux-overview-2.png 590w,\n/static/d189c87b2058252663fecf595debcb01/526de/redux-overview-2.png 885w,\n/static/d189c87b2058252663fecf595debcb01/7bc9a/redux-overview-2.png 1178w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>And finally an action:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d367b84610181b6db7d0876413a22705/837f2/redux-overview-3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 56.06060606060607%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/d367b84610181b6db7d0876413a22705/fb8a0/redux-overview-3.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d367b84610181b6db7d0876413a22705/1a291/redux-overview-3.png 148w,\n/static/d367b84610181b6db7d0876413a22705/2bc4a/redux-overview-3.png 295w,\n/static/d367b84610181b6db7d0876413a22705/fb8a0/redux-overview-3.png 590w,\n/static/d367b84610181b6db7d0876413a22705/526de/redux-overview-3.png 885w,\n/static/d367b84610181b6db7d0876413a22705/837f2/redux-overview-3.png 924w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>This is how an action is structured, it has two properties called <strong>type</strong> and <strong>payload</strong>, where the former says how the state will change and the latter says what will change exactly. But we can’t use this action the way it is, we need to add two more things, declare the type as a constant in another file (we could do it in the same file) and import it, and the next thing is using an <strong>Action Creator</strong> which is just a fancy way of saying that’s a function that returns an Action.</p>\n<h2>Creating our enviroment.</h2>\n<h2>Starting a new project!</h2>\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p><strong>Eng Adrian Beria.</strong></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Redux","date":"February 15, 2020"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/7-Redux/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/6-second-project/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Second Project - Graphing data in state"}},"next":null}}